ball|NFL on ABC]]'' ([[1970 NFL season|1970]]\u2013[[Super Bowl XL|2006]], [[2015\u201316 NFL playoffs|2016]]\u2013present)\n** ''NFL Wild Card Saturday'' ([[1990\u201391 NFL playoffs|1990]]\u2013[[2005\u201306 NFL playoffs|2005]], [[2015\u201316 NFL playoffs|2016]]\u2013present): simulcast of ESPN's NFL Wild Card playoff coverage\n** [[Pro Bowl]] ([[1975 Pro Bowl|1975]]\u2013[[1987 Pro Bowl|1987]], [[1995 Pro Bowl|1995]]\u2013[[2003 Pro Bowl|2003]], [[2018 Pro Bowl|2018]]\u2013present): simulcast of ESPN's Pro Bowl coverage\n** [[National Football League draft|NFL Draft]] (ESPN Day 3 Simulcast 2018\u2013present; self-produced Day 1 and 2 coverage, 2019 present)\n** [[NFL Scouting Combine]] (2019\u2013present)\n* [[XFL (2020)|XFL on ESPN]] (2020\u2013present) \n*''[[Tennis on ESPN]]''\n** [[BNP Paribas Open]] (2011\u201312, 2019)\n** [[The Championships, Wimbledon|Wimbledon]] ([[2012 Wimbledon Championships|2012]]\u2013present): condensed re-broadcasts of ESPN's coverage of Gentlemen's and Ladies' Singles finals, as well as a highlight show on the Championships' rest day\n** [[US Open (tennis)|US Open]]: Arthur Ashe Kids Day\n* [[Overwatch League]] (2019) Stage Semifinals & Finals\n* ''[[Soccer on ESPN]]''\n**[[ESPN Major League Soccer]] on regular season (1996-2008, 2020-present)<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://espnpressroom.com/us/press-releases/2019/12/espn-and-abc-to-televise-31-regular-season-matches-during-major-league-soccers-25th-season/|title=ESPN and ABC to Televise 31 Regular Season Matches during Major League Soccer\u2019s 25th Season|date=2019-12-19|website=ESPN Press Room U.S.|language=en-US|access-date=2020-01-27}}</ref>\n** [[MLS Cup]] (1996\u20132008; 2019\u2013present)<ref>{{cite press release|title=2019 MLS Cup to Air live on ABC and Univision|url=https://www.mlssoccer.com/post/2019/08/28/2019-mls-cup-air-live-abc-and-univision|publisher=MLS Digital|website=MLSSoccer.com|date=August 28, 2019|access-date=August 29, 2019}}</ref>\n** [[UEFA European Championship]] (2008,2020)<ref>{{cite press release|title=ESPN and ABC Present UEFA European Football Championship 2020|url=https://espnpressroom.com/us/press-releases/2019/12/espn-and-abc-present-uefa-european-football-championship-2020/|publisher=ESPN|website=espnpressroom.com|date=December 3, 2019|access-date=December 3, 2019}}</ref> \n* ''[[ESPN College Basketball on ABC]]'' (1962, 1973, 1978, and 1987\u20132014, 2019-present)\n* [[NCAA Women's Gymnastics Championships]] (2020-present)\n* [[Women's College World Series]] (2020-present)\n\n===Additional programming===\n* [[New York City Marathon]] ([[2013 New York City Marathon|2013]]\u2013present): condensed rebroadcast of ESPN2's coverage; coverage simulcast live on [[WABC-TV]] in [[New York metropolitan area|New York]]\n* [[Rose Parade|Tournament of Roses Parade]] (1989\u2013present): produced by ABC Sports from 1989 to 2006 and by ESPN since 2007\n* ''[[ESPY Award]]s'' (2015\u2013present)\n\n===Former programs===\n* ''[[Monday Night Football]]'' ([[1970 NFL season|1970]]\u2013[[2005 NFL season|2005]])\n** [[Super Bowl]]: [[Super Bowl XIX|XIX]], [[Super Bowl XXII|XXII]], [[Super Bowl XXV|XXV]], [[Super Bowl XXIX|XXIX]], [[Super Bowl XXXIV|XXXIV]], [[Super Bowl XXXVII|XXXVII]], and [[Super Bowl XL|XL]]\n** Thursday Night [[National Football League Kickoff game|NFL Kickoff game]] ([[2003 NFL season|2003]]\u2013[[2005 NFL season|2005]])\n* ''[[Major League Baseball on ABC]]''\n** ''[[Major League Baseball Game of the Week]]'' (1953\u20131954, 1960\u20131965)\n** ''[[Monday Night Baseball]]'' (1976\u20131988, telecasts moved to Thursday for 1989)\n** ''[[The Baseball Network|Baseball Night in America]]'' (1994\u20131995)\n** [[World Series]]: {{wsy|1948}}\u2013{{wsy|1950}}, {{wsy|1977}}, {{wsy|1979}}, {{wsy|1981}}, {{wsy|1983}}, {{wsy|1985}}, {{wsy|1987}}, {{wsy|1989}}, and [[1995 World Series|1995 (Games 1, 4, & 5)]]\n* ''[[ESPN College Football on ABC|College Football on ABC]]''\n** [[Sugar Bowl]] ([[1953 Sugar Bowl|1953]]\u2013[[1957 Sugar Bowl|1957]], [[1970 Sugar Bowl|1970]]\u2013[[2006 Sugar Bowl|2006]])\n** [[Rose Bowl Game]] ([[1989 Rose Bowl|1989]]\u2013[[2010 Rose Bowl|2010]])\n** [[Fiesta Bowl]] ([[1999 Fiesta Bowl|1999]]\u2013[[2006 Fiesta Bowl|2006]])\n** [[Orange Bowl (game)|Orange Bowl]] ([[1962 Orange Bowl|1962]]\u2013[[1964 Orange Bowl|1964]], [[1999 Orange Bowl|1999]]\u2013[[2006 Orange Bowl|2006]])\n** [[Gator Bowl]] ([[1965 Gator Bowl (January)|1965]]\u2013[[1968 Gator Bowl|1968]], [[1972 Gator Bowl|1972]]\u2013[[1985 Gator Bowl|1985]] )\n** [[Aloha Bowl]] ([[1986 Aloha Bowl|1986]]\u2013[[2000 Aloha Bowl|2000]])\n** [[Independence Bowl]] ([[1990 Independence Bowl|1990]], [[1991 Independence Bowl|1991]], [[2014 Independence Bowl|2014]])\n** [[Army\u2013Navy Game]] (1954, 1960\u20131961, 1966\u20131981, 1983, 1991\u20131995)\n** [[Peach Bowl]] (1989-1990)\n** [[Liberty Bowl]] (1966-1971, 1976\u20131980, 1995, 2011, 2017)\n** [[Pinstripe Bowl]] (2015)\n** [[Belk Bowl]] (2018)\n** [[Outback Bowl]] (2011-2012, 2017)\n** [[SEC Championship Game]] (1992-2000)\n* ''[[PGA Tour on ABC]]'' (1962\u20132009)\n** [[The Open Championship]] ([[1962 Open Championship|1962]]\u2013[[2009 Open Championship|2009]])\n** [[PGA Championship]] ([[1966 PGA Championship|1966]]\u2013[[1990 PGA Championship|1990]])\n** [[U.S. Open (golf)|U.S. Open]] ([[1966 U.S. Open (golf)|1966]]\u2013[[1994 U.S. Open (golf)|1994]])\n** [[Senior Open Championship]] (1990\u20132009)\n** [[LPGA]] [[Kraft Nabisco Championship]] (1991\u20132005)\n** [[Women's British Open]] (2001\u20132009)\n** [[CME Group Tour Championship]], Final round (2015-2018)\n** ''[[Monday Night Golf]]'' ([[1999 PGA Tour|1999]]\u2013[[2005 PGA Tour|2005]])\n* [[ABC Olympic broadcasts|''Olympics on ABC'']]\n** [[Winter Olympic Games]] ([[1964 Winter Olympics|1964]], [[1968 Winter Olympics|1968]], [[1976 Winter Olympics|1976]], [[1980 Winter Olympics|1980]], [[1984 Winter Olympics|1984]], [[1988 Winter Olympics|1988]])\n** [[Summer Olympic Games]] ([[1968 Summer Olympics|1968]], [[1972 Summer Olympics|1972]], [[1976 Summer Olympics|1976]], [[1984 Summer Olympics|1984]])\n* [[Wide World of Sports (U.S. TV series)|''Wide World of Sports'']] (1961\u20131998 as a series, weekend afternoon programming title 1998\u20132006)\n* ''[[NHL on ABC]]'' ([[1992\u201393 NHL season|1992]]\u2013[[1993\u201394 NHL season|1994]], [[1999\u20132000 NHL season|1999]]\u2013[[2003\u201304 NHL season|2004]])\n* ''[[Thoroughbred Racing on ABC]]''\n** [[Kentucky Derby]] (1975\u20132000)\n** [[Preakness Stakes]] (1977\u20132000)\n** [[Belmont Stakes]] (1986\u20132000, 2006\u20132010)\n** [[Breeders' Cup]] (2008\u20132011)\n* [[American Football League on ABC|American Football League]] ([[1960 American Football League season|1960]]\u2013[[1964 American Football League season|1964]])\n* [[United States Football League]] ([[1983 USFL season|1983]]\u2013[[1985 USFL season|1985]])\n* [[NFL Europe|World League of American Football]] ([[1991 WLAF season|1991]]\u2013[[1992 WLAF season|1992]])\n* ''[[Arena Football League on ESPN]]'' ([[1998 Arena Football League season|1998]]\u2013[[2002 Arena Football League season|2002]], [[2007 Arena Football League season|2007]]\u2013[[2008 Arena Football League season|2008]])\n* [[Continental Football League]] (1966\u20131969)\n* [[North American Soccer League (1968\u20131984)|North American Soccer League]] ([[1979 North American Soccer League season|1979]]\u2013[[1981 North American Soccer League season|1981]])\n* [[FIFA World Cup]] ([[1970 FIFA World Cup|1970]], [[1982 FIFA World Cup|1982]], [[1994 FIFA World Cup|1994]], [[1998 FIFA World Cup|1998]], [[2002 FIFA World Cup|2002]], [[2006 FIFA World Cup|2006]], [[2010 FIFA World Cup|2010]], and [[2014 FIFA World Cup|2014]])\n* [[FIFA Women's World Cup]] ([[1999 FIFA Women's World Cup|1999]], [[2003 FIFA Women's World Cup|2003]])\n* [[Indianapolis 500]] ([[1965 Indianapolis 500|1965]]\u2013[[2018 Indianapolis 500|2018]])\n* ''[[NASCAR on ESPN|NASCAR on ABC]]'' (1961, [[1971 NASCAR Winston Cup Series|1971]], [[1975 NASCAR Winston Cup Series|1975]]\u2013[[1976 NASCAR Winston Cup Series|1976]], [[1979 NASCAR Winston Cup Series|1979]]\u2013[[1982 NASCAR Winston Cup Series|1982]], [[1984 NASCAR Winston Cup Series|1984]]\u2013[[2000 NASCAR Winston Cup Series|2000]], [[2007 NASCAR Nextel Cup Series|2007]]\u2013[[2014 NASCAR Sprint Cup Series|2014]])\n* [[Champ Car|Championship Auto Racing Teams]] ([[1983 CART PPG Indy Car World Series|1983]]\u2013[[2001 CART season|2001]], [[2007 Champ Car season|2007]])\n* ''[[IndyCar Series on ABC]]'' ([[1996 Indy Racing League season|1996]]\u2013[[2018 IndyCar Series|2018]])\n* [[International Race of Champions]] ([[IROC I|1974]]\u2013[[IROC VII|1980]], [[IROC XI|1987]]\u2013[[IROC XXVII|2003]])\n* [[American Le Mans Series]] ([[2008 American Le Mans Series season|2008]]\u2013[[2009 American Le Mans Series season|2009]], [[2011 American Le Mans Series season|2011]]\u2013[[2013 American Le Mans Series season|2013]])\n* ''[[Fight of the Week]]'' (1960\u20131964)\n* ''[[Professional Bowlers Tour]]'' (1962\u20131997)\n* [[Superstars (US Version)|''The Superstars'']] (1973\u20131984, 1991\u20131994, 1998\u20132002)\n* ''[[The American Sportsman]]'' (1965\u20131986)\n* [[Scripps National Spelling Bee]] ([[79th Scripps National Spelling Bee|2006]]\u2013[[83rd Scripps National Spelling Bee|2010]])\n* ''[[ESPN Sports Saturday]]'' (2010\u20132015)\n\n==Personalities==\n\n===Current===\n\n====Play-by-play====\n* ''[[NBA on ABC]]'' \u2013 [[Mike Breen]], [[Mark Jones (sportscaster)|Mark Jones]], [[Dave Pasch]], [[Ryan Ruocco]], [[Adam Amin]]\n* ''[[Monday Night Football]] Simulcast (Wild Card & Pro Bowl)'' \u2013 [[Joe Tessitore]]\n* ''[[WNBA on ESPN]]'' \u2013 [[Ryan Ruocco]]\n* ''[[ESPN College Football on ABC]] and [[Saturday Night Football]]'' \u2013 [[Chris Fowler]], [[Rece Davis]], [[Sean McDonough]], [[Steve Levy]], [[Bob Wischusen]], [[Dave Pasch]], [[Dave Flemming]], [[Adam Ami